content:
@Hixie
> e.g. animation and text, and batch

I doubt that text should be supported in vector format meant for the app assets — as practically all contemporary apps must support i18n. This is supported by Flutter on the widget level. Any text that is used for symbolic purposes within drawings will be turned to vectors by designer anyway. Dealing with text would add much bloat for no apparent gain. IMO, it would be much more useful to support addressable layers within. Eg, for having programttically composable variants (think added star badge or similar).
